5.1. Fees and Payment Terms

The Customer shall pay an annual subscription fee ("Subscription Fee") of one hundred eighty thousand U.S. dollars ($180,000) exclusive of any applicable taxes, which shall be paid as follows:

(a) The Subscription Fee is payable annually in advance by bank transfer or other mutually agreed method within thirty (30) calendar days from receipt of an invoice issued by the Supplier;

(b) All payments due under this Agreement shall be made without deduction, set-off, counterclaim, or abatement whatsoever except as expressly provided herein;

(c) If the Customer fails to make any payment when due, the unpaid amount will accrue interest at a rate equal to one and a half percent (1.5%) per month until fully paid up, calculated daily based on a year of three hundred sixty-five (365) days;

(d) The Supplier may suspend access to the Services if the Customer does not make full payment within fourteen (14) days following delivery of written notice requesting such payment;

(e) The Customer acknowledges that it is responsible for all taxes imposed by law related to its use of the Services, including but not limited to sales, value added, goods and services, consumption, and similar taxes, excluding only those taxes based solely upon the income of the Supplier. Any such taxes shall be billed separately by the Supplier and paid directly to the relevant authority by the Customer.

END OF CLAUSE TEXT
